## Educational Use Disclaimer

This project contains educational material about security vulnerabilities and
attack techniques. The scripts, documentation, and examples provided are for:

✓ AUTHORIZED USE ONLY
✓ Educational and training purposes
✓ Security research in controlled environments
✓ Improving defensive security capabilities

✗ DO NOT USE FOR
✗ Unauthorized access to computer systems
✗ Any illegal activities
✗ Causing harm or damage

Unauthorized access to computer systems violates laws including but not limited to:
- Computer Fraud and Abuse Act (CFAA) - 18 U.S.C. § 1030 (United States)
- Computer Misuse Act 1990 (United Kingdom)
- Similar cybercrime laws in other jurisdictions

Users of this software are solely responsible for ensuring their use complies
with all applicable laws and regulations.

## Security Research Ethics

When conducting security research:
1. Always obtain explicit written authorization
2. Define clear scope and boundaries
3. Report vulnerabilities responsibly
4. Respect privacy and confidentiality
5. Cause no harm to systems or data

For more information on responsible disclosure:
- https://www.cisa.gov/coordinated-vulnerability-disclosure-process
- https://www.iso.org/standard/72311.html (ISO/IEC 29147)

## Data Privacy Notice

All employee data, Social Security Numbers, and personal information shown in
this simulation are ENTIRELY FICTIONAL. No real individuals were involved, and
all data was created specifically for educational purposes.

This project respects data privacy laws including:
- GDPR (General Data Protection Regulation)
- CCPA (California Consumer Privacy Act)
- HIPAA (Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act)
- Other applicable privacy regulations

## Attribution

This educational project was created as part of a digital forensics training
program. While based on realistic attack scenarios, all events, companies, and
individuals are simulated for educational purposes only.

If you use this material in your own training or presentations:
- Provide attribution to this repository
- Maintain all disclaimer and educational use notices
- Ensure your use also complies with educational purposes

## Contact & Responsible Disclosure

If you discover any issues with the educational content or have suggestions
for improvement, please open an issue in this repository.

For security concerns about the educational materials themselves, please
contact the repository maintainers privately before public disclosure.
